  "texts": [
    "Therefore in the sum over G G in the last line of Eq. 126, we only keep the terms G G = 0, -b G1, -b G2, where the b Gi are the monolayer reciprocal lattice vectors shown in Fig.",
    "These are the three terms for which t(p + G1 G) has the smallest argument-effectively we have kept the lowest harmonic of the moiré potential (dominant harmonic approximation).",
    "Its value is approximated as t(|K|).",
    "The delta function constrains G ′ G to take the same three reciprocal lattice vectors if we demand that |p ′ -K 2 | remains smallfoot_54.",
    "Aggregating these observations and performing some straightforward algebra, we obtain the BM model presented in Sec."
  ]
}